{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":442,"text":"On January 4, 1934,"},{"time":4513,"text":"a young man delivered a report"},{"time":7529,"text":"to the United States Congress"},{"time":9914,"text":"that 80 years on,"},{"time":11868,"text":"still shapes the lives of\neveryone in this room today,"},{"time":16528,"text":"still shapes the lives of\neveryone on this planet."},{"time":22222,"text":"That young man wasn't a politician,"},{"time":25102,"text":"he wasn't a businessman,"},{"time":27101,"text":"a civil rights activist"},{"time":28438,"text":"or a faith leader."},{"time":30213,"text":"He was that most unlikely of heroes,"},{"time":33484,"text":"an economist."},{"time":37007,"text":"His name was Simon Kuznets"},{"time":39552,"text":"and the report that \nhe delivered was called"},{"time":42696,"text":"\"National Income, 1929-1932.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":47148,"text":"Now, you might think"},{"time":48632,"text":"this is a rather dry and dull report."},{"time":51723,"text":"And you're absolutely right."},{"time":53805,"text":"It's dry as a bone."},{"time":56260,"text":"But this report is the foundation"},{"time":58570,"text":"of how, today, we judge the \nsuccess of countries:"},{"time":61503,"text":"what we know best as\nGross Domestic Product,"},{"time":65052,"text":"GDP."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67363,"text":"GDP has defined and shaped our lives"},{"time":70266,"text":"for the last 80 years."},{"time":72864,"text":"And today I want to talk about \n"},{"time":74681,"text":"a different way to measure\nthe success of countries,"},{"time":78520,"text":"a different way to define \nand shape our lives"},{"time":81669,"text":"for the next 80 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84926,"text":"But first, we have to understand"},{"time":86817,"text":"how GDP came to\ndominate our lives."},{"time":90726,"text":"Kuznets' report was delivered"},{"time":92986,"text":"at a moment of crisis."},{"time":94708,"text":"The U.S. economy was plummeting"},{"time":96734,"text":"into the Great Depression"},{"time":98349,"text":"and policy makers were \nstruggling to respond."},{"time":101434,"text":"Struggling because they didn't\nknow what was going on."},{"time":104579,"text":"They didn't have data and statistics."},{"time":107961,"text":"So what Kuznet's report gave them"},{"time":110783,"text":"was reliable data on what \nthe U.S. economy"},{"time":114061,"text":"was producing,"},{"time":115196,"text":"updated year by year."},{"time":118264,"text":"And armed with this information,"},{"time":120604,"text":"policy makers were, eventually,"},{"time":122612,"text":"able to find a way out \nof the slump."},{"time":126040,"text":"And because Kuznets' invention"},{"time":127922,"text":"was found to be so useful,"},{"time":129694,"text":"it spread around the world."},{"time":131382,"text":"And now today, every country"},{"time":133851,"text":"produces GDP statistics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136815,"text":"But, in that first report,"},{"time":139922,"text":"Kuznets himself delivered a warning."},{"time":143466,"text":"It's in the introductory chapter."},{"time":145447,"text":"On page seven he says,"},{"time":147481,"text":"\"The welfare of a nation can, therefore,"},{"time":150110,"text":"scarcely be inferred"},{"time":151664,"text":"from a measurement of \nnational income"},{"time":153664,"text":"as defined above.\""},{"time":155601,"text":"It's not the greatest sound \nbite in the world,"},{"time":158969,"text":"and it's dressed up in the cautious \nlanguage of the economist."},{"time":162598,"text":"But his message was clear:"},{"time":164774,"text":"GDP is a tool"},{"time":166508,"text":"to help us measure\neconomic performance."},{"time":169566,"text":"It's not a measure\nof our well-being."},{"time":172534,"text":"And it shouldn't be a guide \nto all decision making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177351,"text":"But we have ignored Kuznets' warning."},{"time":180221,"text":"We live in a world where"},{"time":181777,"text":"GDP is the benchmark of success"},{"time":184900,"text":"in a global economy."},{"time":187177,"text":"Our politicians boast when\nGDP goes up."},{"time":190406,"text":"Markets move"},{"time":191690,"text":"and trillions of dollars of capital"},{"time":193564,"text":"move around the world"},{"time":194988,"text":"based on which countries\nare going up"},{"time":196739,"text":"and which countries \nare going down,"},{"time":198580,"text":"all measured in GDP."},{"time":201204,"text":"Our societies have become"},{"time":202533,"text":"engines to create more GDP."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206908,"text":"But we know that GDP is flawed."},{"time":210443,"text":"It ignores the environment."},{"time":212973,"text":"It counts bombs and prisons as progress."},{"time":216629,"text":"It can't count happiness or community."},{"time":219878,"text":"And it has nothing to say \nabout fairness or justice."},{"time":224621,"text":"Is it any surprise that our world,"},{"time":227324,"text":"marching to the drumbeat of GDP,"},{"time":230155,"text":"is teetering on the brink\nof environmental disaster"},{"time":233432,"text":"and filled with anger and conflict?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":236938,"text":"We need a better way\nto measure our societies,"},{"time":241341,"text":"a measure based on the real \nthings that matter to real people."},{"time":246724,"text":"Do I have enough to eat?"},{"time":248686,"text":"Can I read and write?"},{"time":250762,"text":"Am I safe?"},{"time":252500,"text":"Do I have rights?"},{"time":254655,"text":"Do I live in a society where\nI'm not discriminated against?"},{"time":257784,"text":"Is my future and the future of my children \nprevented from environmental destruction?"},{"time":264222,"text":"These are questions that GDP"},{"time":266113,"text":"does not and cannot answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271016,"text":"There have, of course,"},{"time":272535,"text":"been efforts in the past"},{"time":273921,"text":"to move beyond GDP."},{"time":276563,"text":"But I believe that we're living"},{"time":277938,"text":"in a moment when we"},{"time":279212,"text":"are ready for a measurement revolution."},{"time":282952,"text":"We're ready because we've seen,"},{"time":285628,"text":"in the financial crisis of 2008,"},{"time":287862,"text":"how our fetish for economic growth"},{"time":290681,"text":"led us so far astray."},{"time":292712,"text":"We've seen, in the Arab Spring,"},{"time":295096,"text":"how countries like Tunisia"},{"time":296941,"text":"were supposedly economic superstars,"},{"time":299691,"text":"but they were societies"},{"time":301216,"text":"that were seething with discontentment."},{"time":304495,"text":"We're ready, because today\nwe have the technology"},{"time":308183,"text":"to gather and analyze data"},{"time":310498,"text":"in ways that would have been\nunimaginable to Kuznets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314545,"text":"Today, I'd like to introduce you \nto the Social Progress Index."},{"time":319428,"text":"It's a measure of the \nwell-being of society,"},{"time":322155,"text":"completely separate from GDP."},{"time":324912,"text":"It's a whole new way\nof looking at the world."},{"time":328569,"text":"The Social Progress Index"},{"time":330179,"text":"begins by defining what it"},{"time":331502,"text":"means to be a good society"},{"time":333449,"text":"based around three dimensions."},{"time":336940,"text":"The first is, does everyone have\nthe basic needs for survival:"},{"time":341035,"text":"food, water, shelter, safety?"},{"time":343885,"text":"Secondly, does everyone have"},{"time":346605,"text":"access to the building blocks \nto improve their lives:"},{"time":349436,"text":"education, information, health\nand sustainable environment?"},{"time":353948,"text":"And then third, does every \nindividual have access"},{"time":357632,"text":"to a chance to pursue their goals"},{"time":360412,"text":"and dreams and ambitions"},{"time":362260,"text":"free from obstacles?"},{"time":363417,"text":"Do they have rights,"},{"time":364964,"text":"freedom of choice,"},{"time":366353,"text":"freedom from discrimination"},{"time":367875,"text":"and access to the the world's\nmost advanced knowledge?"},{"time":371336,"text":"Together, these 12 components"},{"time":374700,"text":"form the Social Progress framework."},{"time":378035,"text":"And for each of these 12 components,"},{"time":380123,"text":"we have indicators to measure \nhow countries are performing."},{"time":383554,"text":"Not indicators of effort or intention,"},{"time":386683,"text":"but real achievement."},{"time":388931,"text":"We don't measure how much\na country spends on healthcare,"},{"time":392133,"text":"we measure the length and \nquality of people's lives."},{"time":396446,"text":"We don't measure whether governments\npass laws against discrimination,"},{"time":401045,"text":"we measure whether people \nexperience discrimination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405475,"text":"But what you want to know"},{"time":406835,"text":"is who's top, don't you?\n(Laughter)"},{"time":409851,"text":"I knew that, I knew that, I knew that."},{"time":411668,"text":"Okay, I'm going to show you."},{"time":413194,"text":"I'm going to show you on this chart."},{"time":415590,"text":"So here we are,"},{"time":416934,"text":"what I've done here is put on the \nvertical axis social progress."},{"time":421146,"text":"Higher is better."},{"time":422481,"text":"And then, just for comparison,"},{"time":424503,"text":"just for fun,"},{"time":425825,"text":"on the horizontal axis\nis GDP per capita."},{"time":429693,"text":"Further to the right is more."},{"time":431583,"text":"So the country in the world"},{"time":434737,"text":"with the highest social progress,"},{"time":438127,"text":"the number one country on social progress"},{"time":441486,"text":"is New Zealand."},{"time":444882,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":448398,"text":"Well done! Never been; must go."},{"time":451215,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":453537,"text":"The country with the least social progress,"},{"time":456399,"text":"I'm sorry to say, is Chad."},{"time":458716,"text":"I've never been; maybe next year."},{"time":461638,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":463447,"text":"Or maybe the year after."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465639,"text":"Now, I know what you're thinking."},{"time":467212,"text":"You're thinking, \"Aha,"},{"time":468592,"text":"but New Zealand has a higher GDP"},{"time":470988,"text":"than Chad!\""},{"time":472850,"text":"It's a good point, well made."},{"time":475344,"text":"But let me show you"},{"time":476806,"text":"two other countries."},{"time":478069,"text":"Here's the United States —"},{"time":480495,"text":"considerably richer than New Zealand,"},{"time":483242,"text":"but with a lower level of social progress."},{"time":485688,"text":"And then here's Senegal —"},{"time":488340,"text":"it's got a higher level of \nsocial progress than Chad,"},{"time":492337,"text":"but the same level of GDP."},{"time":494286,"text":"So what's going on? Well, look."},{"time":496035,"text":"Let me bring in the rest of \nthe countries of the world,"},{"time":498536,"text":"the 132 we've been able to measure,"},{"time":500744,"text":"each one represented by a dot."},{"time":503082,"text":"There we go. Lots of dots."},{"time":504581,"text":"Now, obviously I can't do all of them,"},{"time":506323,"text":"so a few highlights for you:"},{"time":508056,"text":"The highest ranked G7 country is Canada."},{"time":512876,"text":"My country, the United Kingdom,"},{"time":514980,"text":"is sort of middling, sort of dull,"},{"time":517697,"text":"but who cares —"},{"time":519062,"text":"at least we beat the French."},{"time":521240,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":528737,"text":"And then looking at the \nemerging economies,"},{"time":531004,"text":"top of the BRICS, \npleased to say, is Brazil."},{"time":534338,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":536044,"text":"Come on, cheer!"},{"time":537831,"text":"Go, Brazil!"},{"time":539773,"text":"Beating South Africa,"},{"time":541306,"text":"then Russia,"},{"time":542599,"text":"then China"},{"time":543733,"text":"and then India."},{"time":545307,"text":"Tucked away on the right-hand side,"},{"time":547672,"text":"you will see a dot of a \ncountry with a lot of GDP"},{"time":551025,"text":"but not a huge amount \nof social progress —"},{"time":552968,"text":"that's Kuwait."},{"time":554946,"text":"Just above Brazil"},{"time":556637,"text":"is a social progress superpower —"},{"time":558956,"text":"that's Costa Rica."},{"time":560456,"text":"It's got a level of social progress the same \nas some Western European countries,"},{"time":564431,"text":"with a much lower GDP."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566400,"text":"Now, my slide is getting \na little cluttered"},{"time":568682,"text":"and I'd like to step back a bit."},{"time":570364,"text":"So let me take away these countries,"},{"time":571818,"text":"and then pop in the regression line."},{"time":574732,"text":"So this shows the average relationship"},{"time":576385,"text":"between GDP and social progress."},{"time":578896,"text":"The first thing to notice,"},{"time":581138,"text":"is that there's lots of noise"},{"time":582993,"text":"around the trend line."},{"time":584690,"text":"And what this shows,"},{"time":586275,"text":"what this empirically demonstrates,"},{"time":589157,"text":"is that GDP is not destiny."},{"time":592192,"text":"At every level of GDP per capita,"},{"time":595395,"text":"there are opportunities\nfor more social progress,"},{"time":598593,"text":"risks of less."},{"time":600596,"text":"The second thing to notice"},{"time":602056,"text":"is that for poor countries,"},{"time":604559,"text":"the curve is really steep."},{"time":606532,"text":"So what this tells us is that"},{"time":607807,"text":"if poor countries can get"},{"time":609060,"text":"a little bit of extra GDP,"},{"time":610954,"text":"and if they reinvest that"},{"time":612737,"text":"in doctors, nurses, water supplies,"},{"time":615409,"text":"sanitation, etc.,"},{"time":616782,"text":"there's a lot of social progress bang"},{"time":618801,"text":"for your GDP buck."},{"time":620387,"text":"And that's good news, and that's what \nwe've seen over the last 20, 30 years,"},{"time":623962,"text":"with a lot of people lifted out of poverty"},{"time":625963,"text":"by economic growth and good policies"},{"time":628173,"text":"in poorer countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630045,"text":"But go on a bit further up the curve,"},{"time":632242,"text":"and then we see it flattening out."},{"time":634351,"text":"Each extra dollar of GDP"},{"time":636603,"text":"is buying less and less social progress."},{"time":639839,"text":"And with more and more\nof the world's population"},{"time":642513,"text":"living on this part of the curve,"},{"time":645076,"text":"it means GDP is becoming"},{"time":647300,"text":"less and less useful"},{"time":649084,"text":"as a guide to our development."},{"time":651600,"text":"I'll show you an example of Brazil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653747,"text":"Here's Brazil:"},{"time":654970,"text":"social progress of about 70 out of 100,"},{"time":657841,"text":"GDP per capita about \n14,000 dollars a year."},{"time":660335,"text":"And look, Brazil's above the line."},{"time":663256,"text":"Brazil is doing a reasonably good job"},{"time":665142,"text":"of turning GDP into social progress."},{"time":668467,"text":"But where does Brazil go next?"},{"time":670454,"text":"Let's say that Brazil"},{"time":671966,"text":"adopts a bold economic plan"},{"time":673738,"text":"to double GDP in the next decade."},{"time":676041,"text":"But that is only half a plan."},{"time":679657,"text":"It's less than half a plan,"},{"time":681934,"text":"because where does Brazil\nwant to go on social progress?"},{"time":685186,"text":"Brazil, it's possible"},{"time":687504,"text":"to increase your growth,"},{"time":689239,"text":"increase your GDP,"},{"time":690816,"text":"while stagnating or going backwards"},{"time":692706,"text":"on social progress."},{"time":694055,"text":"We don't want Brazil"},{"time":695241,"text":"to become like Russia."},{"time":696973,"text":"What you really want is for Brazil"},{"time":699288,"text":"to get ever more efficient at creating \nsocial progress from its GDP,"},{"time":704241,"text":"so it becomes more like New Zealand."},{"time":706539,"text":"And what that means is that"},{"time":708119,"text":"Brazil needs to prioritize social progress"},{"time":710776,"text":"in its development plan"},{"time":712468,"text":"and see that it's not just growth alone,"},{"time":714880,"text":"it's growth with social progress."},{"time":717532,"text":"And that's what the Social \nProgress Index does:"},{"time":720150,"text":"It reframes the debate about development,"},{"time":722760,"text":"not just about GDP alone,"},{"time":724820,"text":"but inclusive, sustainable growth"},{"time":727399,"text":"that brings real improvements \nin people's lives."},{"time":731818,"text":"And it's not just about countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734394,"text":"Earlier this year,"},{"time":737184,"text":"with our friends from the Imazon \nnonprofit here in Brazil,"},{"time":741751,"text":"we launched the first subnational \nSocial Progress Index."},{"time":746408,"text":"We did it for the Amazon region."},{"time":748868,"text":"It's an area the size of \nEurope, 24 million people,"},{"time":752656,"text":"one of the most deprived \nparts of the country."},{"time":755084,"text":"And here are the results,"},{"time":756994,"text":"and this is broken down"},{"time":758629,"text":"into nearly 800 different municipalities."},{"time":762133,"text":"And with this detailed information"},{"time":763816,"text":"about the real quality of life"},{"time":766034,"text":"in this part of the country,"},{"time":767977,"text":"Imazon and other partners"},{"time":769957,"text":"from government, \nbusiness and civil society"},{"time":772286,"text":"can work together to construct"},{"time":774000,"text":"a development plan"},{"time":775677,"text":"that will help really improve\npeople's lives,"},{"time":778014,"text":"while protecting that \nprecious global asset"},{"time":781250,"text":"that is the Amazon Rainforest."},{"time":784221,"text":"And this is just the beginning,"},{"time":786122,"text":"You can create a Social Progress Index"},{"time":788501,"text":"for any state, region, \ncity or municipality."},{"time":793656,"text":"We all know and love TEDx;"},{"time":795729,"text":"this is Social Pogress-x."},{"time":797971,"text":"This is a tool for anyone to come and use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801165,"text":"Contrary to the way we \nsometimes talk about it,"},{"time":804045,"text":"GDP was not handed down from \nGod on tablets of stone. (Laughter)"},{"time":810365,"text":"It's a measurement tool\ninvented in the 20th century"},{"time":814360,"text":"to address the challenges\nof the 20th century."},{"time":819152,"text":"In the 21st century,"},{"time":821004,"text":"we face new challenges:"},{"time":823456,"text":"aging, obesity, climate change, and so on."},{"time":826564,"text":"To face those challenges,"},{"time":828223,"text":"we need new tools of measurement,"},{"time":830243,"text":"new ways of valuing progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833997,"text":"Imagine if we could measure"},{"time":836395,"text":"what nonprofits, charities,"},{"time":838925,"text":"volunteers, civil society organizations"},{"time":840894,"text":"really contribute to our society."},{"time":844700,"text":"Imagine if businesses competed"},{"time":847768,"text":"not just on the basis of\ntheir economic contribution,"},{"time":851179,"text":"but on their contribution \nto social progress."},{"time":855003,"text":"Imagine if we could hold \npoliticians to account"},{"time":858950,"text":"for really improving people's lives."},{"time":863146,"text":"Imagine if we could work together —"},{"time":866131,"text":"government, business, \ncivil society, me, you —"},{"time":871199,"text":"and make this century the \ncentury of social progress."},{"time":876704,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":877783,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}